comments.raw_text:
Ran across this code:

http://mxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/widget/src/cocoa/nsMenuBarX.mm#465

 464 // Do what is necessary to conform to the Aqua guidelines for menus.
 465 void nsMenuBarX::AquifyMenuBar()
 466 {
 467   nsCOMPtr<nsIDOMDocument>
         domDoc(do_QueryInterface(mContent->GetDocument()));
 468   if (domDoc) {
 469     // remove the "About..." item and its separator
 470     HideItem(domDoc, NS_LITERAL_STRING("aboutSeparator"), nsnull);
 471     HideItem(domDoc, NS_LITERAL_STRING("aboutName"),
           getter_AddRefs(mAboutItemContent));
 ...

I suspect this is just old cruft (and some of it seems like deadwood now). We should just use CSS to control the visibility of these menu items on OSX.

